#include <iostream>
#include <fstream>
#include <string>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    string word; // word to search for
    int count = 0; // count of occurrences

    // read word to search for
    cout << "Enter word to search for: ";
    cin >> word;

    // open file for reading
    ifstream inputFile("input.txt");

    // read each line of the file
    string line;
    while (getline(inputFile, line)) {
        // split line into words
        vector<string> words = split(line, ' ');

        // count occurrences of word in line
        for (string w : words) {
            if (w == word) {
                count++;
            }
        }
    }

    // print result
    cout << "Word " << word << " occurred " << count << " times." << endl;

    return 0;
}

This program uses the ifstream class to open a file for reading and getline() to read each line of the file. The split() function is used to split each line into words, and the for loop iterates over each word in the line to count the occurrences of the specified word. Finally, the result is printed to the console.

Note that this is a simple example and can be expanded upon to handle more complex scenarios, such as handling special characters, multiple files, or searching for multiple words.
